## What the Process Looks Like

**Step 1 — Discovery call (30 minutes).** You share your business model, target audience, conversion goals, and existing content. This shapes the map's scope so every page serves a business objective — not just a search term.

**Step 2 — Research and mapping (5–7 working days).** I analyse your full topic space, competitor content gaps, query network relationships, and search demand to build the complete content architecture. Entity-attribute pairs are developed for every page, each with measurable search intent.

**Step 3 — Delivery and walkthrough (60 minutes).** You receive all 6 deliverables — the processed topical map with title tags, URL slugs, meta descriptions, internal linking matrix, and publication schedule — plus a call to explain priorities and answer questions.

**One-off deliverable. No monthly retainer required.** You own the complete content architecture to implement at your own pace — or commission [content briefs](/services/content-briefs/) for each page as the next step.

